TY  - JOUR
T1  - Note—An Approximate Algorithm for Multidimensional Zero-One Knapsack Problems—A Parametric Approach
AU  - Lee, Jae Sik
AU  - Guignard, Monique
Y1  - 1988/03/01
PY  - 1988
DA  - 1988/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.34.3.402
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.34.3.402
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 402
EP  - 410
VL  - 34
IS  - 3
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - A new approximate algorithm for multidimensional zero-one knapsack problems with all positive coefficients is presented. The procedure is controlled by three parameters which affect the tradeoff between solution quality and computation time and whose values are set by the users. For 48 test problems with 5 to 20 constraints and 6 to 500 variables, the solution found was on the average within 0.34% of the optimum and the computation time was the shortest compared with three other well-known heuristics.
AB  - A new approximate algorithm for multidimensional zero-one knapsack problems with all positive coefficients is presented. The procedure is controlled by three parameters which affect the tradeoff between solution quality and computation time and whose values are set by the users. For 48 test problems with 5 to 20 constraints and 6 to 500 variables, the solution found was on the average within 0.34% of the optimum and the computation time was the shortest compared with three other well-known heuristics.
